Gluster 3.2: Launching Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance from Template[
Launching Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance from Template>>]

This section describes how to install Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance
for Xen.

*To install the Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance*

1.  Download the Xen Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance from
https://store.gluster.com/788/catalog/category.5837/language.en/currency.USD/?id=v3XNw3616z[here] +
 +
2.  Extract the downloaded file to the server. The following file will
be available: +
 +
- Gluster-Virtual-Storage-Appliance--3-2-0-Template.xva +
 +
3.  Launch the Citrix XenCenter. The XenCenter main screen appears. +
 +
4.  Select the Xen Server from the list. The *Connect to Server* dialog
may appear if the Remember Password option is not selected. +
 +
Image:Gluster-32-vsa-xen-install1.jpg +
 +
5.  Provide login credentials and click *Connect*. The XenCenter main
screen appears.
6.  Choose *File > Import*. The *Import* wizard launches. +
 +
Image:Gluster-32-vsa-xen-install2.jpg[550px] +
 +
7.  Browse and select the Gluster XVA and click *Next*. +
 +
Image:Gluster-32-vsa-xen-install3.jpg +
 +
8.  Follow the on-screen instructions and in *Select a home server for
the new VM* screen, select the home server and click *Next*. +
 +
Image:Gluster-32-vsa-xen-install6.jpg[550px] +
 +
9.  In *Configure virtual network interfaces for the new VM* screen,
select the network and click *Next*. +
 +
 Image:Gluster-32-vsa-xen-install7.jpg[550px] +
 +
10. Click *Finish* in *Complete the import* screen to complete the
wizard. +
 +
Image:Gluster-32-vsa-xen-install8.jpg[625px] +
 +
After you complete the wizard, the appliance is downloaded and added to
the XenServer host virtual machine inventory as
*Gluster-Virtual-Storage-Appliance-3-2-0-Template*.

